<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">662.6331/78a: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-03-30T17:00:00-05:00">March 30, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>14. The projected Austro-German customs union is being carefully studied
                            here. In what manner and to what extent will Austro-American trade
                            relations be affected by the proposed union? You are to utilize the
                            services of the Commercial Attaché and the Consul General in this
                            search. We expect a telegraphic summary to precede a lengthy report.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>